HEADWORD: Jarring
<hw>Jar"ring</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Jar.</er>]</ety> <def>Shaking; disturbing; discordant.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧A jarring sound.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jarring</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Jarring
<hw>Jar"ring</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A shaking; a tremulous
motion; <as>as, the <ex>jarring</ex> of a steamship, caused by its
engines</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Discord; a clashing of interests.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧Endless <xex>jarrings</xex> and immortal hate.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jarringly</ent>⟦br⟧
